Generally, chapter 11 are for organizations to "reorganize" themselves and to get concessions from creditors, the debt is not forgiven, merely postponed/restructured.  Individuals like a relative of mine filed for chapter 7 to clear off whatever assets they have to clear of their debts.

And the higher education act of 1976, both federal and private student loans are not dischargeable in bankruptcy. they are caveats, but for the most part, no dice, your still saddled with student loans till you pay it off.

https://www.americanbar.org/groups/business\_law/safeborrowing/student/bankruptcy/#:\~:text=For%20cases%20filed%20on%20and,your%20family%2C%20and%20your%20dependents.
